<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="119e4f02-0a38-5ed3-982f-ae9903818fe6" activityNameId="a55b3076-140d-4388-80a5-2375b6324edb" parentActivityId="e57262b7-d10d-4057-a92e-705fde5df9d0" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">cement production, Portland SR3</activityName>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">CEM SR3</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Sulfate Resistant Cement SR3</synonym>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">From the reception of raw materials at the cement factory.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en"> This activity ends with the Portland cement SR3 produced in the cement silos (after milling). The dataset does not include packaging and administration</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The information details the manufacturing of CEM SR3 using milled limestone and gypsum as fillers.The dataset describes the production of cement (CEM SR3). Tunisia has five types of cement (CEM I to CEM V) based on the supplementary cementitious materials (limestone).</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">CEM SR3 is a Sulphate Resistant Cement that is made by 95-90% of clinker and mixed with 5 to 10% of limestone.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">Portland SR3 production process consists of four main steps: (1) Quarrying of limestone and other  raw materials to the processing plant. (2) Preparation of “raw meal” for pyroprocessing (3) Pyroprocessing of raw materials to produce clinker using the dry process. (4) Final grinding of the clinker together with inter-grinding with a small proportion of gypsum to produce Portland SR3 cement. Steps (1) to (4) are not considered in dataset.</text>
          <imageUrl index="3">https://db3.ecoinvent.org/images/910a96c9-7e41-4964-9381-bbf6f05378f1</imageUrl>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="4">NT47.01(2017): Ciment - Partie 1: Composition, spécifications et critères des conformité des ciments courants</text>
          <imageUrl index="5">https://db3.ecoinvent.org/images/c24830b9-1c17-4970-90f3-d8882650b85b</imageUrl>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="36cd730c-4485-4fe9-8efe-8850f771796d">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2394:Manufacture of cement, lime and plaster</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="133fc02a-7d7e-11de-9ae2-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">TN</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The dataset represents the production of Sulfate Resistant Cement (CEM SR3) in Tunisia.</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">In Tunisia, all cement production is through dry kiln process. The clinker (90-95%) is ground with gypsum (3-5%) and depending on the type of cement and technical standard (NT-47.01 2017 Eqv EN 197-1) with other materials such as limestone (5 to 10%)  to sulfate resistant cement cement.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2019-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Time period corresponds to data collection period (2019).</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
