    <modellingAndValidation>
      <representativeness systemModelId="290c1f85-4cc4-4fa1-b0c8-2cb7f4276dce" percent="15.0">
        <systemModelName xml:lang="en">Allocation, cut-off by classification</systemModelName>
        <samplingProcedure xml:lang="en">Data represent 15% of Tunisia's 2019 cement production. Using confidential surveys, one cement manufacturer gave information on the production of cement in 2019. The manufacturer's estimated cement composition is represented by the weighted average of raw material flows. Since manufacturers did not provide the production amounts of each kind of cement owing to privacy issues, the weighting factor utilized is the overall volume of cement produced. The yearly average of the manufacturer unit flows was calculated for additional input flows, such as grinding aids, equipment maintenance supplies, fuels and power. With the exception of the grinding aids, all other flows' consumption is given for the whole cement plant, which often makes several types of cement. Manufacturer information on fuel usage was provided in terms of mass or volume. To make the dataset simpler and to take into account the accompanying air emissions, they were transformed into energy using their lower heating values and modeled as a heat input. The "cement Portland/GLO" information was used to estimate the infrastructure input flow (cement plant) (accessed 15.09.2022). The weighted average of the sample was taken into consideration while calculating the exchange amounts. In order to maintain consistency with other EcoInvent datasets, no conversion to the geometric mean of the lognormal distribution was performed.
</samplingProcedure>
        <extrapolations xml:lang="en">Data represent 15% of Tunisian cement production. This sample is extrapolated to reflect total output in the country. The primary values are regarded appropriate for a typical production of Sulfate Resistant Cement in Tunisia.</extrapolations>
      </representativeness>
